    This class is the top layer, multi thread safe, interface for: loading, opening or create and initialise an ontology (see OWLLibrary and OWLReferencesInterface). As well as mainpulating the structure (see OWLManipulator) and quering the resoner. (see OWLManipulator).

      • saveOntology

        public void saveOntology(boolean exportInf)
        It will save an ontology into a file. The files path is retrieved from the OWLReferences class using: ontoRef.getIriFilePath();. Note that this procedure may replace an already existing file. The exporting of the asserted relation is done by: InferredAxiomExporter.exportOntology(OWLReferences) and my be an expensive procedure.
        Parameters:
        exportInf - if true export all reasoner inferences in the returned ontology References. Otherwise it just call OWLReferencesInterface.saveOntology()

      • saveOntology

        public void saveOntology(boolean exportInf,
                         java.lang.String filePath)
        It will save an ontology into a file. The files path is given as input parameter, and this method does not update: ontoRef.getIriFilePath();. Note that this procedure may replace an already existing file. The exporting of the asserted relation is done by: InferredAxiomExporter.exportOntology(OWLReferences) and my be an expensive procedure.
        Parameters:
        exportInf - if true export all reasoner inferences in the returned ontology References. Otherwise it just call OWLReferencesInterface.saveOntology(String)
        filePath - directory in which save the ontology.
